1
00:01:37,110 --> 00:01:40,150
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,170 --> 00:01:43,210
[Episode 23]

3
00:01:44,009 --> 00:01:44,670
Is it the two towns

4
00:01:44,670 --> 00:01:46,330
that lost their water supply?

5
00:01:46,810 --> 00:01:47,420
Yes.

6
00:01:49,190 --> 00:01:50,330
We found the cause.

7
00:01:51,420 --> 00:01:52,590
Large-scale mining

8
00:01:52,870 --> 00:01:53,259
will

9
00:01:53,289 --> 00:01:54,170
definitely affect

10
00:01:54,170 --> 00:01:55,500
the groundwater table.

11
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:56,350
Sand and gravel

12
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:57,170
extraction

13
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,600
widens the river channel

14
00:01:59,039 --> 00:02:01,150
and increases its drainage capacity.

15
00:02:01,150 --> 00:02:02,320
So the river reaches

16
00:02:02,340 --> 00:02:02,910
the dry season earlier

17
00:02:02,910 --> 00:02:04,760
and drops to lower-than-normal levels.

18
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:05,420
Simply put,

19
00:02:05,420 --> 00:02:06,210
it could lead

20
00:02:06,230 --> 00:02:07,760
to groundwater depletion.

21
00:02:08,250 --> 00:02:09,690
A bit late for that, isn't it?

22
00:02:09,690 --> 00:02:11,300
Why didn't you say that earlier?

23
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:12,190
It was in a geography exam.

24
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:14,050
But I only remembered when I saw it.

25
00:02:14,050 --> 00:02:15,170
I've always said

26
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:16,310
that you should come out here

27
00:02:16,310 --> 00:02:17,680
to take the exam.

28
00:02:19,530 --> 00:02:21,060
Once we seize the gold mine,

29
00:02:21,650 --> 00:02:23,120
the 90,000 they owe us

30
00:02:23,140 --> 00:02:24,180
have to be taken

31
00:02:24,210 --> 00:02:25,140
from their gold.

32
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:26,460
You really are

33
00:02:26,460 --> 00:02:27,660
obsessed with money.

34
00:02:28,590 --> 00:02:29,430
90,000?

35
00:02:29,820 --> 00:02:30,880
That's too little.

36
00:02:32,010 --> 00:02:33,140
Let's take them down

37
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:35,440
and grab all the gold.

38
00:02:36,329 --> 00:02:36,970
I agree.

39
00:02:58,610 --> 00:02:59,300
Sangba.

40
00:03:02,750 --> 00:03:03,580
Go back

41
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,370
and take the map and the note

42
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,530
to County Mayor Lin.

43
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:07,910
And get armed police

44
00:03:07,910 --> 00:03:10,650
and public security personnel here
as soon as possible.

45
00:03:10,650 --> 00:03:11,330
A round trip

46
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,760
takes at least four days.

47
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,890
We'll wait for you here.

48
00:03:14,930 --> 00:03:15,500
Okay, Captain.

49
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:16,230
Don't worry.

50
00:03:16,590 --> 00:03:18,120
Give them a submachine gun.

51
00:03:19,510 --> 00:03:21,170
Here's an extra barrel of gas.

52
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,500
You can drink it if you run out of water.

53
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:24,390
You jinx.

54
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:25,300
You're giving me this much;

55
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:25,970
you won't have enough.

56
00:03:25,970 --> 00:03:28,300
We don't have enough gas
to go back anyway.

57
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:29,360
Sangba.

58
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:32,579
We're all counting on you.

59
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:33,620
Got it.

60
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:48,680
Okay.

61
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:18,620
Tell me.

62
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:20,880
Why don't you eat meat?

63
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:24,430
Haven't you heard it from them?

64
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:26,450
I want to hear it from you.

65
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:30,610
I used to hunt antelopes, you know?

66
00:04:31,630 --> 00:04:32,780
I hunted so many

67
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:35,440
that I lost count.

68
00:04:36,450 --> 00:04:37,210
One day,

69
00:04:38,220 --> 00:04:39,620
in the Uninhabited Zone,

70
00:04:40,130 --> 00:04:41,930
I got caught in a heavy snowstorm

71
00:04:42,540 --> 00:04:43,870
and fell into a snow pit.

72
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:46,300
Do you know

73
00:04:46,940 --> 00:04:47,970
what it means to fall

74
00:04:47,970 --> 00:04:48,830
into a snow pit?

75
00:04:50,659 --> 00:04:51,120
Then how

76
00:04:51,130 --> 00:04:52,060
did you survive?

77
00:04:53,810 --> 00:04:56,550
Tibetan antelopes
are very afraid of humans.

78
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:00,350
In that snow pit,

79
00:05:01,170 --> 00:05:02,330
there were many of them

80
00:05:02,330 --> 00:05:03,390
huddled together.

81
00:05:04,100 --> 00:05:06,100
I fell right into the middle of them.

82
00:05:06,510 --> 00:05:08,570
Maybe they were afraid of dying, too.

83
00:05:08,770 --> 00:05:10,370
They surrounded me tightly.

84
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:12,070
Later,

85
00:05:13,310 --> 00:05:15,240
I was saved by the Mountain Patrol.

86
00:05:16,010 --> 00:05:16,870
Since then,

87
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:19,780
I've never eaten meat again.

88
00:05:26,630 --> 00:05:27,630
How can you steal?

89
00:05:27,750 --> 00:05:28,890
How can you steal?

90
00:05:28,930 --> 00:05:29,270
I...

91
00:05:29,290 --> 00:05:30,290
How can you steal?

92
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:31,960
I only have a little left.

93
00:05:32,710 --> 00:05:33,390
Nonsense.

94
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:34,710
I saw a huge bottle

95
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:36,720
under your bed.

96
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:38,500
That big bottle is off-limits.

97
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,230
I'm saving that for my wedding.

98
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:42,290
You've been on so many blind dates.

99
00:05:42,450 --> 00:05:43,510
You'll never

100
00:05:43,530 --> 00:05:44,510
get a chance to drink it.

101
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:44,830
You...

102
00:05:44,830 --> 00:05:45,860
You jinx!

103
00:05:45,950 --> 00:05:46,680
Ask Captain.

104
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,480
You jinx!

105
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:48,150
Zhacuo!

106
00:05:51,420 --> 00:05:51,870
Bai!

107
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:52,830
Hand it over.

108
00:05:53,810 --> 00:05:54,540
He Qingyuan.

109
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:56,950
Be generous.

110
00:05:57,830 --> 00:05:58,690
If you keep hiding the wine,

111
00:05:58,690 --> 00:06:00,250
how will you ever find a wife?

112
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:01,630
Let's make an exception today.

113
00:06:01,630 --> 00:06:02,490
Everyone has a drink.

114
00:06:02,490 --> 00:06:03,900
Great.

115
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:04,960
Okay.

116
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:15,380
Nice wine, Han.

117
00:06:18,890 --> 00:06:19,970
It's good.

118
00:06:21,370 --> 00:06:22,970
I only grab it. I don't drink.

119
00:06:23,070 --> 00:06:23,600
Captain.

120
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:27,930
Smells great.

121
00:06:29,810 --> 00:06:30,190
Here.

122
00:06:36,570 --> 00:06:37,070
Shao.

123
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:39,500
Come on, have a sip.

124
00:06:47,590 --> 00:06:48,610
You wasted it.

125
00:06:49,320 --> 00:06:50,980
What's there to fight over it?

126
00:06:51,770 --> 00:06:52,250
You...

127
00:06:52,570 --> 00:06:53,040
If you're not drinking,

128
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:54,190
why waste it?

129
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:56,520
It tastes bad.

130
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:02,370
Look here.

131
00:07:02,950 --> 00:07:04,720
Victory is in sight.

132
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:06,370
Let's look to the future.

133
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:07,700
Let me interview you.

134
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:10,360
Deputy Captain He,

135
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:11,350
you go first.

136
00:07:13,820 --> 00:07:14,820
What should I say?

137
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,640
After the gold mine is closed

138
00:07:16,930 --> 00:07:19,130
and the nature reserve is established,

139
00:07:19,390 --> 00:07:20,520
what are your plans?

140
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:22,980
Of course, I'll stay in the reserve

141
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:23,980
and keep working.

142
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:27,720
We'll be well-equipped then.

143
00:07:28,610 --> 00:07:29,500
We'll have so many jeeps,

144
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,360
we won't be able to count them all.

145
00:07:31,890 --> 00:07:32,420
As for me,

146
00:07:32,420 --> 00:07:34,390
I'll sit in the office,

147
00:07:34,770 --> 00:07:35,450
drink tea,

148
00:07:36,010 --> 00:07:37,070
and keep the books.

149
00:07:38,070 --> 00:07:40,130
Just thinking about it is wonderful.

150
00:07:43,460 --> 00:07:44,790
Zhacuo, what about you?

151
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:48,960
Me?

152
00:07:51,420 --> 00:07:53,620
My dad wants me to go back and herd sheep.

153
00:07:54,610 --> 00:07:55,930
But I think

154
00:07:57,300 --> 00:07:58,020
herding Tibetan antelopes

155
00:07:58,020 --> 00:07:59,350
is pretty much the same.

156
00:08:01,110 --> 00:08:02,850
I'll gather the sick ones

157
00:08:03,430 --> 00:08:05,330
and the lost little ones

158
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,430
all together

159
00:08:07,290 --> 00:08:09,150
and open a kindergarten for them.

160
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,510
That's called...

161
00:08:15,050 --> 00:08:16,580
conservation work, right?

162
00:08:21,010 --> 00:08:22,140
Han, it's your turn.

163
00:08:22,950 --> 00:08:24,190
I have nothing to say.

164
00:08:24,260 --> 00:08:25,580
I'll listen to Captain.

165
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:26,440
I'll do whatever

166
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:27,140
he says.

167
00:08:28,950 --> 00:08:29,810
Stop laughing.

168
00:08:29,870 --> 00:08:30,770
Bai Ju,

169
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:31,980
it's your turn.

170
00:08:36,309 --> 00:08:38,440
I want to set up a forestry police unit,

171
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,000
and ideally get

172
00:08:40,030 --> 00:08:41,620
a helicopter too.

173
00:08:42,789 --> 00:08:44,910
With forty thousand square kilometers,

174
00:08:44,910 --> 00:08:46,040
we could finish a patrol

175
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:47,040
in one day.

176
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:48,250
Then just fly

177
00:08:48,250 --> 00:08:49,240
straight back to the county

178
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:50,570
and go home for a shower.

179
00:08:51,730 --> 00:08:52,930
That would be so nice.

180
00:08:53,980 --> 00:08:54,600
A helicopter

181
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:57,000
would scare the Tibetan antelopes, right?

182
00:09:01,180 --> 00:09:02,110
What a buzzkill.

183
00:09:02,710 --> 00:09:03,210
Well,

184
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:05,550
I'll stick to driving then.

185
00:09:11,010 --> 00:09:11,540
Captain,

186
00:09:13,310 --> 00:09:15,110
it's your turn to give a summary.

187
00:09:16,770 --> 00:09:17,340
Wait.

188
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:22,140
Actually, I don't really have

189
00:09:22,140 --> 00:09:22,930
a summary.

190
00:09:23,690 --> 00:09:25,150
Everyone spoke very well.

191
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:26,870
But I can talk about

192
00:09:26,870 --> 00:09:27,580
my dream.

193
00:09:28,910 --> 00:09:29,700
Captain,

194
00:09:30,190 --> 00:09:31,050
why do you change your clothes

195
00:09:31,050 --> 00:09:32,550
for the interview?

196
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:33,630
Cairen gave me

197
00:09:33,630 --> 00:09:34,620
this jacket.

198
00:09:39,030 --> 00:09:40,360
Since we're going on TV,

199
00:09:40,770 --> 00:09:41,720
I put it on

200
00:09:41,980 --> 00:09:43,180
to make Cairen happy.

201
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:49,630
Let me talk about my dream.

202
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:53,360
I hope that in the future,

203
00:09:54,130 --> 00:09:55,480
the world won't need

204
00:09:55,510 --> 00:09:56,970
nature reserves anymore.

205
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,550
No more nature reserves?

206
00:10:05,660 --> 00:10:06,220
Shut up.

207
00:10:08,050 --> 00:10:09,120
If one day,

208
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:11,550
Bolamula

209
00:10:11,580 --> 00:10:12,500
can fully recover

210
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:13,900
its vitality and beauty,

211
00:10:16,810 --> 00:10:17,640
I hope

212
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:21,410
it will no longer need armed patrols

213
00:10:22,630 --> 00:10:23,320
and no longer need

214
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,860
to be fenced off

215
00:10:25,290 --> 00:10:27,020
in the name of a nature reserve.

216
00:10:27,670 --> 00:10:29,320
I hope people will truly

217
00:10:29,830 --> 00:10:31,480
protect it from their hearts,

218
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,430
respect it,

219
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:34,100
and appreciate it.

220
00:10:35,740 --> 00:10:36,620
People can quietly

221
00:10:36,620 --> 00:10:37,910
stay by its side,

222
00:10:39,290 --> 00:10:40,030
and it

223
00:10:40,870 --> 00:10:42,230
can forever soothe

224
00:10:42,730 --> 00:10:43,810
people's souls.

225
00:11:28,540 --> 00:11:30,340
Why aren't you saying anything?

226
00:11:30,580 --> 00:11:31,980
You usually talk so much.

227
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,600
How did you know it was me?

228
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:34,900
My intuition.

229
00:11:36,180 --> 00:11:38,040
I was just thinking you'd show up,

230
00:11:38,650 --> 00:11:39,790
and then you did.

231
00:11:40,830 --> 00:11:42,490
So you were thinking of me.

232
00:11:49,950 --> 00:11:51,070
I think I just

233
00:11:53,010 --> 00:11:54,680
saw my parents.

234
00:11:59,190 --> 00:12:00,340
Don't scare me.

235
00:12:08,210 --> 00:12:08,740
I feel like

236
00:12:08,740 --> 00:12:09,960
they're watching me.

237
00:12:11,580 --> 00:12:12,980
When I was little, my mom,

238
00:12:14,210 --> 00:12:15,540
Director Zhang, told me

239
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,970
that if I ever missed my birth parents,

240
00:12:19,630 --> 00:12:21,430
I could just look up at the stars.

241
00:12:22,790 --> 00:12:23,890
But back then,

242
00:12:24,980 --> 00:12:26,010
I just thought

243
00:12:26,570 --> 00:12:28,230
that was just to comfort kids.

244
00:12:28,980 --> 00:12:30,510
So why do you believe it now?

245
00:12:35,290 --> 00:12:36,340
Maybe

246
00:12:39,010 --> 00:12:42,010
I started to believe it
after entering the mountains.

247
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:44,980
Whenever I see the starry sky,

248
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,900
I can't help but think of them.

249
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:50,620
That's actually

250
00:12:50,650 --> 00:12:51,550
a instinct.

251
00:12:53,270 --> 00:12:54,560
Those stars are,

252
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:56,690
in a way,

253
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,150
our mothers.

254
00:12:59,770 --> 00:13:00,700
What do you mean?

255
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:01,390
We are all made of

256
00:13:01,390 --> 00:13:02,990
the same matter as the stars.

257
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:05,540
We are one way

258
00:13:06,250 --> 00:13:07,680
for the universe

259
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:08,650
to know itself.

260
00:13:10,660 --> 00:13:11,740
You're making that up, right?

261
00:13:11,740 --> 00:13:12,820
No, that's real.

262
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:13,960
And it wasn't me.

263
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:14,380
A

264
00:13:14,410 --> 00:13:16,140
foreign astronomer said that.

265
00:13:17,890 --> 00:13:18,980
And I believe,

266
00:13:21,370 --> 00:13:21,870
when you're

267
00:13:21,870 --> 00:13:23,340
gazing at the stars,

268
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:27,180
the stars are looking at you, too.

269
00:13:28,820 --> 00:13:29,700
Maybe,

270
00:13:30,350 --> 00:13:32,070
in some part of the universe,

271
00:13:32,790 --> 00:13:34,200
you and your parents

272
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:35,510
are talking right now.

273
00:13:39,850 --> 00:13:40,860
Then, I wonder

274
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:42,970
what we'd talk about.

275
00:13:48,460 --> 00:13:50,840
About you going to the police academy.

276
00:13:51,770 --> 00:13:52,600
About

277
00:13:53,340 --> 00:13:54,270
Bolamula.

278
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:58,290
About environmental protection.

279
00:14:01,390 --> 00:14:02,100
If there's time,

280
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:03,300
maybe even about me.

281
00:14:08,290 --> 00:14:09,700
Sometimes I forget...

282
00:14:11,580 --> 00:14:12,910
how I got here.

283
00:14:15,770 --> 00:14:17,040
I forget what I went through

284
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:18,460
in the past twenty years.

285
00:14:20,650 --> 00:14:21,700
And I even forget

286
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,050
who I am.

287
00:14:25,130 --> 00:14:25,800
It feels like

288
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:27,330
ever since I was conscious,

289
00:14:28,540 --> 00:14:29,590
I've been here.

290
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:34,960
I've become

291
00:14:34,980 --> 00:14:37,040
a stone at the foot of a snow mountain,

292
00:14:39,430 --> 00:14:41,070
or a Tibetan antelope

293
00:14:43,980 --> 00:14:45,360
running forever

294
00:14:48,010 --> 00:14:49,350
on this wasteland.

295
00:15:01,870 --> 00:15:02,500
According to

296
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:04,030
that astronomer's theory,

297
00:15:05,870 --> 00:15:06,510
people,

298
00:15:08,050 --> 00:15:08,980
stones,

299
00:15:10,130 --> 00:15:11,390
and Tibetan antelopes

300
00:15:12,170 --> 00:15:14,030
aren't actually that different.

301
00:15:14,810 --> 00:15:16,170
We are all just

302
00:15:16,300 --> 00:15:17,830
tiny parts of the universe.

303
00:15:18,980 --> 00:15:20,780
Eventually, we'll become stars

304
00:15:21,190 --> 00:15:22,390
and return to the sky,

305
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:24,100
right?

306
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:26,740
Sometimes,

307
00:15:29,740 --> 00:15:30,790
forgetting is a form

308
00:15:30,790 --> 00:15:31,990
of self-protection.

309
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:34,550
But whether you

310
00:15:34,660 --> 00:15:35,900
remember it or not,

311
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:39,140
everything you've experienced

312
00:15:39,770 --> 00:15:41,300
and every step you've taken

313
00:15:42,040 --> 00:15:43,590
has shaped who you are now.

314
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:48,120
You don't have to try
to remember anything.

315
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:49,770
Because those experiences

316
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:51,310
are already

317
00:15:51,340 --> 00:15:52,270
part of you.

318
00:15:55,220 --> 00:15:56,460
Talking big again.

319
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:58,140
Just treat it as big talk then.

320
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:00,540
But I think

321
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,770
we are like this starry sky.

322
00:16:03,670 --> 00:16:05,120
It seems chaotic.

323
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:07,380
But every star

324
00:16:07,410 --> 00:16:08,700
has its own path.

325
00:16:12,690 --> 00:16:14,550
We may not see the future clearly,

326
00:16:15,150 --> 00:16:17,210
but as long as we walk boldly forward,

327
00:16:17,390 --> 00:16:19,590
we will definitely find our direction.

328
00:16:20,570 --> 00:16:21,430
What about you?

329
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:23,810
What is your direction?

330
00:16:33,030 --> 00:16:34,430
Mine is the same as yours.

331
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:37,220
Bolamula.

332
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:39,460
This land.

333
00:16:40,930 --> 00:16:41,790
The starry sky.

334
00:16:45,070 --> 00:16:45,740
And you.

335
00:17:50,700 --> 00:17:51,960
Jiumei. Jiumei. Jiumei.

336
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:52,750
Look ahead.

337
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:55,760
Good morning.

338
00:19:01,380 --> 00:19:02,250
You're getting good at this.

339
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:02,600
Here.

340
00:19:02,630 --> 00:19:04,960
You're almost catching up to He Qingyuan.

341
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:07,100
Here.

342
00:19:07,150 --> 00:19:08,940
Wash up with hot water.

343
00:19:11,180 --> 00:19:13,220
You're giving me special treatment again.

344
00:19:13,220 --> 00:19:14,950
Special treatment for ladies.

345
00:19:16,940 --> 00:19:17,350
Here.

346
00:19:20,330 --> 00:19:20,980
I think

347
00:19:21,050 --> 00:19:21,990
you are the one best suited

348
00:19:21,990 --> 00:19:23,210
to handle logistics.

349
00:19:27,940 --> 00:19:28,350
I'm telling you,

350
00:19:28,350 --> 00:19:29,250
I might not be as good at

351
00:19:29,250 --> 00:19:30,510
fixing cars as you guys,

352
00:19:30,510 --> 00:19:31,680
but I'm a great shot.

353
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:33,120
Compared to whom?

354
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:34,550
Zhacuo?

355
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:36,440
Save us some bullets.

356
00:19:36,570 --> 00:19:37,330
I'm not comparing myself to him.

357
00:19:37,330 --> 00:19:38,840
I only compete with myself.

358
00:19:38,840 --> 00:19:40,300
I've made great progress.

359
00:19:47,270 --> 00:19:48,420
How is it?

360
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:49,460
Is it good?

361
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:52,300
Better than raw.

362
00:19:56,350 --> 00:19:56,960
Who is it?

363
00:19:58,610 --> 00:20:00,440
Come up, quick!

364
00:20:00,620 --> 00:20:01,350
Wake them up.

365
00:20:02,850 --> 00:20:04,450
Wake up. Something's wrong.

366
00:20:13,510 --> 00:20:14,010
The second truck

367
00:20:14,010 --> 00:20:15,210
looks like Sangba's.

368
00:20:15,430 --> 00:20:16,200
No way.

369
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:19,140
The gas barrels on the truck bed are ours.

370
00:20:20,140 --> 00:20:21,120
It is ours.

371
00:20:27,180 --> 00:20:27,640
Then...

372
00:20:27,750 --> 00:20:28,100
the truck is there.

373
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:28,870
Where are they?

374
00:20:28,870 --> 00:20:30,470
Where are Sangba and Jiumei?

375
00:20:43,330 --> 00:20:44,060
It's Sangba.

376
00:20:44,380 --> 00:20:44,910
It's him.

377
00:20:45,280 --> 00:20:46,480
Jiumei is there, too.

378
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:52,790
No.

379
00:20:52,810 --> 00:20:53,730
They're going in.

380
00:20:53,730 --> 00:20:54,310
Get the guns!

381
00:20:54,310 --> 00:20:54,960
Stop them!

382
00:20:55,090 --> 00:20:56,290
Liu, start the truck!

383
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:57,000
Stop them!

384
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:58,210
Let's go!

385
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:58,770
Get in!

386
00:20:59,160 --> 00:20:59,680
Let's go!

387
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:00,490
Stop Zhacuo!

388
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:01,850
Zhacuo!

389
00:21:03,140 --> 00:21:03,720
Go quickly!

390
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:04,300
Go help!

391
00:21:04,330 --> 00:21:06,200
Stop arguing!

392
00:21:06,910 --> 00:21:07,920
You called me a jinx

393
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,420
and that summoned the bad luck!

394
00:21:09,420 --> 00:21:10,570
I won't say it anymore!

395
00:21:10,570 --> 00:21:11,010
Quiet.

396
00:21:11,090 --> 00:21:11,620
Quiet.

397
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:13,420
Quiet.

398
00:21:13,710 --> 00:21:14,520
I'll stop shouting.

399
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:15,170
I'll stop.

400
00:21:24,850 --> 00:21:25,430
Captain.

401
00:21:30,740 --> 00:21:32,260
Put all the gas in one truck.

402
00:21:32,260 --> 00:21:33,350
Liu, drive back to the county town.

403
00:21:33,350 --> 00:21:34,330
I'm not leaving.

404
00:21:36,570 --> 00:21:37,510
I don't dare.

405
00:21:46,830 --> 00:21:47,540
I know

406
00:21:48,880 --> 00:21:49,450
you've never

407
00:21:49,450 --> 00:21:50,710
driven this far alone.

408
00:21:51,780 --> 00:21:52,850
But many things

409
00:21:53,350 --> 00:21:53,860
won't wait

410
00:21:53,860 --> 00:21:54,990
until you're ready.

411
00:21:57,670 --> 00:21:59,170
You are

412
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:00,840
our only hope now.

413
00:22:11,030 --> 00:22:13,030
We don't know the situation inside.

414
00:22:13,380 --> 00:22:14,310
How many people?

415
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:15,600
How many weapons?

416
00:22:16,100 --> 00:22:16,930
If we go in blindly—

417
00:22:16,930 --> 00:22:17,930
It'll be too late.

418
00:22:20,260 --> 00:22:21,860
A round trip takes four days.

419
00:22:22,460 --> 00:22:24,020
That's without getting stuck

420
00:22:24,020 --> 00:22:25,350
or hitting a snowstorm.

421
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,380
If we keep waiting,

422
00:22:32,470 --> 00:22:33,870
they will be dead by then.

423
00:23:31,380 --> 00:23:32,560
Open the roadblock.

424
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:37,140
I'm Duojie.

425
00:25:33,650 --> 00:25:34,850
You're Li Yongqiang.

426
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:36,080
County Mayor Duo.

427
00:25:36,420 --> 00:25:37,560
We meet again.

428
00:25:44,270 --> 00:25:44,880
What are you people

429
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:46,000
doing out here?

430
00:25:48,170 --> 00:25:49,260
You saw it.

431
00:25:49,830 --> 00:25:51,760
It's just a small-scale business,

432
00:25:51,880 --> 00:25:53,140
quarrying some stone.

433
00:25:57,210 --> 00:25:58,340
Do you have a permit?

434
00:25:58,670 --> 00:25:59,820
I'll apply

435
00:25:59,840 --> 00:26:00,700
when I get back.

436
00:26:01,180 --> 00:26:02,230
I'll handle it immediately.

437
00:26:02,230 --> 00:26:02,820
No need.

438
00:26:04,330 --> 00:26:06,530
Submit the application directly to me.

439
00:26:06,550 --> 00:26:07,220
Let's talk.

440
00:26:07,460 --> 00:26:08,240
No problem.

441
00:26:09,570 --> 00:26:10,530
Let's go inside

442
00:26:11,590 --> 00:26:12,350
and talk.

443
00:26:12,560 --> 00:26:13,560
You caught my men.

444
00:26:16,510 --> 00:26:17,640
Release them first.

445
00:26:50,500 --> 00:26:51,070
Move.

446
00:27:08,070 --> 00:27:09,070
What's your name?

447
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:11,580
Zhang Yuan.

448
00:27:13,510 --> 00:27:15,040
Is Zhang Yang your brother?

449
00:27:16,050 --> 00:27:16,600
Yes.

450
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:17,530
He is.

451
00:27:17,630 --> 00:27:18,490
Do you know him?

452
00:27:23,350 --> 00:27:23,910
I do.

453
00:27:24,500 --> 00:27:24,920
Miss.

454
00:27:25,010 --> 00:27:25,550
I beg you.

455
00:27:25,570 --> 00:27:26,420
Please take me with you.

456
00:27:26,420 --> 00:27:27,220
They killed everyone

457
00:27:27,220 --> 00:27:27,790
who tried to run.

458
00:27:27,790 --> 00:27:28,480
I'm terrified.

459
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,270
Please save me.

460
00:27:29,270 --> 00:27:29,760
Officer,

461
00:27:29,760 --> 00:27:30,700
I want to go home too!

462
00:27:30,700 --> 00:27:31,420
I want to leave, too.

463
00:27:31,420 --> 00:27:32,070
I want to go home too.

464
00:27:32,070 --> 00:27:33,130
Shut up, all of you.

465
00:27:34,260 --> 00:27:34,720
Don't move!

466
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:35,780
What are you doing?

467
00:27:35,960 --> 00:27:37,020
What are you doing?

468
00:27:37,500 --> 00:27:38,010
Drop it!

469
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:39,250
Drop the gun!

470
00:27:39,480 --> 00:27:40,160
Drop the gun!

471
00:27:40,160 --> 00:27:40,630
Don't move!

472
00:27:40,630 --> 00:27:41,360
Drop the gun!

473
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:44,170
Drop the gun!

474
00:27:44,380 --> 00:27:45,010
Don't move!

475
00:27:45,010 --> 00:27:45,740
Drop the gun!

476
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:46,850
This is Mazhi County‘s territory!

477
00:27:46,850 --> 00:27:47,910
Put down your guns!

478
00:27:48,860 --> 00:27:50,720
Does the county have jurisdiction here?

479
00:27:50,720 --> 00:27:51,720
I'll teach you a lesson for your father!

480
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:52,250
Put down!

481
00:27:52,270 --> 00:27:52,790
I'll kill you!

482
00:27:52,790 --> 00:27:53,750
Put it down, or I'll shoot!

483
00:27:53,750 --> 00:27:54,550
Shoot me then!

484
00:27:54,610 --> 00:27:56,070
Put it down, or I'll shoot!

485
00:27:56,070 --> 00:27:56,750
Nobody moves!

486
00:27:56,750 --> 00:27:57,410
Don't move!

487
00:27:59,940 --> 00:28:00,580
Police!

488
00:28:00,610 --> 00:28:01,270
Don't move!

489
00:28:01,510 --> 00:28:02,030
Police!

490
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:03,210
Nobody moves!

491
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:04,010
I'm a police officer.

492
00:28:04,010 --> 00:28:05,070
I have full authority here.

493
00:28:05,070 --> 00:28:06,520
Put down your guns, everyone!

494
00:28:06,520 --> 00:28:08,450
There's no need for conflict here.

495
00:28:09,030 --> 00:28:09,880
Whoever shoots

496
00:28:09,880 --> 00:28:10,510
goes to prison.

497
00:28:10,510 --> 00:28:11,570
No one will escape!

498
00:28:31,630 --> 00:28:32,360
Listen to me.

499
00:28:33,930 --> 00:28:34,990
Put down your guns.

500
00:28:39,830 --> 00:28:41,230
I'll put mine down first.

501
00:29:20,850 --> 00:29:21,440
Dongzi.

502
00:29:28,980 --> 00:29:29,510
Stand up!

503
00:29:37,420 --> 00:29:38,420
County Mayor Duo.

504
00:29:40,070 --> 00:29:41,220
I can let this kid

505
00:29:41,970 --> 00:29:43,060
and your team members

506
00:29:43,060 --> 00:29:44,230
go.

507
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:46,020
But I'm a businessman.

508
00:29:46,660 --> 00:29:47,740
Mutual benefit.

509
00:29:47,760 --> 00:29:49,150
Then we're friends.

510
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:51,180
Before you go,

511
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:53,080
I want to talk to you

512
00:29:53,190 --> 00:29:54,450
about a partnership.

513
00:29:56,190 --> 00:29:56,690
Okay.

514
00:29:57,220 --> 00:29:57,720
Please.

515
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:18,360
County Mayor Duo.

516
00:30:19,680 --> 00:30:21,410
Your head's worth two million.

517
00:30:22,670 --> 00:30:23,680
I could buy your life

518
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:24,720
for two million.

519
00:30:24,740 --> 00:30:26,200
But I don't want to do that.

520
00:30:26,790 --> 00:30:28,450
I want to make friends with you

521
00:30:29,250 --> 00:30:30,550
with this money.

522
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:31,940
Li Yongqiang.

523
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:33,920
You've killed my men.

524
00:30:34,180 --> 00:30:35,100
As long as you don't interfere

525
00:30:35,100 --> 00:30:36,100
with my business,

526
00:30:36,530 --> 00:30:38,240
my people will steer clear

527
00:30:38,390 --> 00:30:39,520
of your patrols

528
00:30:39,610 --> 00:30:41,010
in the Uninhabited Zone.

529
00:30:42,310 --> 00:30:43,440
You've got it wrong.

530
00:30:44,110 --> 00:30:45,030
I didn't come here

531
00:30:45,030 --> 00:30:46,030
to make arrests.

532
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:49,320
I'm here to deliver a notice.

533
00:30:54,460 --> 00:30:55,570
What notice?

534
00:30:59,770 --> 00:31:00,950
We both know

535
00:31:01,140 --> 00:31:02,020
what lies beneath

536
00:31:02,020 --> 00:31:02,620
Bolamula.

537
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:04,680
The county's next step

538
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:06,610
is to build a development zone here

539
00:31:07,090 --> 00:31:09,290
and regulate the gold mining industry.

540
00:31:10,460 --> 00:31:11,240
As long as you cooperate

541
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:11,970
and pull out,

542
00:31:12,350 --> 00:31:13,610
I can promise you this:

543
00:31:14,550 --> 00:31:15,820
Once the development zone is established,

544
00:31:15,820 --> 00:31:18,420
we'll prioritize
issuing you a mining permit.

545
00:31:19,030 --> 00:31:21,230
The location will still be Mount Qimar.

546
00:31:21,270 --> 00:31:22,400
When the time comes,

547
00:31:22,960 --> 00:31:24,690
you can operate out in the open.

548
00:31:38,150 --> 00:31:39,150
I don't trust you.

549
00:31:42,210 --> 00:31:43,420
Aren't you afraid

550
00:31:45,450 --> 00:31:47,380
you won't make it out of here today?

551
00:31:53,110 --> 00:31:54,770
Do you take me for a fossicker?

552
00:32:01,250 --> 00:32:02,670
I'm a member of the Mazhi County Party
Standing Committee,

553
00:32:02,670 --> 00:32:03,870
Deputy County Mayor,

554
00:32:04,140 --> 00:32:06,940
and Manager
of the Economic Development Company.

555
00:32:07,610 --> 00:32:09,070
You think killing me here

556
00:32:10,780 --> 00:32:12,040
means no one will care?

557
00:32:12,120 --> 00:32:13,380
Then what do you think—

558
00:32:14,430 --> 00:32:16,260
that I can mine gold here

559
00:32:17,610 --> 00:32:19,270
all on my own?

560
00:32:26,990 --> 00:32:27,660
Eat slowly.

561
00:32:31,770 --> 00:32:32,430
Slow down.

562
00:32:37,570 --> 00:32:38,680
Do you know where

563
00:32:38,700 --> 00:32:39,960
the hostages are held?

564
00:32:42,700 --> 00:32:44,200
There's a dugout

565
00:32:44,540 --> 00:32:45,870
behind that shed ahead.

566
00:32:46,310 --> 00:32:47,050
The captives

567
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:48,450
are all locked in there.

568
00:33:49,650 --> 00:33:51,920
The one who caught me
in the Uninhabited Zone

569
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:52,680
was him.

570
00:33:53,900 --> 00:33:55,010
Do you know

571
00:33:55,040 --> 00:33:56,470
who he's talking about?

572
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:21,310
Get down!

573
00:34:41,389 --> 00:34:42,120
Come back!

574
00:34:44,190 --> 00:34:45,710
Hide! Hide!

575
00:34:48,670 --> 00:34:49,290
Han!

576
00:34:49,670 --> 00:34:50,150
Han!

577
00:34:51,050 --> 00:34:51,630
Han!

578
00:35:37,690 --> 00:35:38,340
Han.

579
00:35:39,990 --> 00:35:40,530
Let's go!

580
00:35:43,570 --> 00:35:44,090
Sangba!

581
00:35:44,510 --> 00:35:45,170
Jiumei!

582
00:35:47,620 --> 00:35:48,220
Sangba.

583
00:36:20,410 --> 00:36:20,940
Captain!

584
00:36:20,940 --> 00:36:21,340
Bai Ju!

585
00:36:21,900 --> 00:36:22,440
Captain!

586
00:36:22,610 --> 00:36:23,000
Get in!

587
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:23,460
Zhacuo!

588
00:36:23,780 --> 00:36:24,480
Don't go!

589
00:36:24,500 --> 00:36:24,940
Zhacuo,

590
00:36:24,940 --> 00:36:25,280
come back!

591
00:36:25,280 --> 00:36:25,810
Hurry up.

592
00:36:25,860 --> 00:36:26,260
Get in!

593
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:27,690
Get in, quick.

594
00:36:38,780 --> 00:36:39,350
Get down.

595
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:40,840
Help, quick.

596
00:36:40,840 --> 00:36:41,900
Come down and help.

597
00:36:53,470 --> 00:36:54,550
Han, drive!

598
00:37:03,400 --> 00:37:04,600
-Let's go!
-Let's go!

599
00:37:04,610 --> 00:37:05,810
-Let's go!
-Let's go!

600
00:37:13,740 --> 00:37:14,720
Get in, quick!

601
00:37:14,900 --> 00:37:15,700
Get in, quick!

602
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:19,940
Captain, let's go!

603
00:37:19,940 --> 00:37:20,350
Get in!

604
00:37:20,380 --> 00:37:20,910
Let's go!

605
00:37:21,650 --> 00:37:22,590
Shao Yunfei!

606
00:37:22,610 --> 00:37:23,550
Shao Yunfei!

607
00:37:27,270 --> 00:37:27,850
Captain!

608
00:37:28,450 --> 00:37:29,110
Get in.

609
00:37:45,090 --> 00:37:45,630
Get down!

610
00:37:46,010 --> 00:37:46,610
Stay down!

611
00:37:53,290 --> 00:37:54,100
Give me a gun!

612
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:56,610
Let's go!

613
00:37:57,510 --> 00:37:58,040
Let's go!

614
00:37:59,110 --> 00:37:59,690
Stop the car!

615
00:37:59,690 --> 00:38:00,750
Stop the car first!

616
00:38:00,820 --> 00:38:01,760
Stop!

617
00:38:02,380 --> 00:38:03,320
Get in, quick!

618
00:38:03,550 --> 00:38:04,080
Let's go!

619
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:08,530
Are you okay?

620
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:09,570
I'm fine.

621
00:41:00,150 --> 00:41:03,350
[Two weeks later]

622
00:41:00,810 --> 00:41:02,390
The Qima'er Gold Mine

623
00:41:02,420 --> 00:41:03,340
in Bolamula

624
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:04,530
has been sealed off.

625
00:41:05,110 --> 00:41:06,940
During this operation,

626
00:41:07,030 --> 00:41:08,560
the police arrested

627
00:41:08,590 --> 00:41:10,050
12 suspects,

628
00:41:10,900 --> 00:41:12,730
rescued 47

629
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:13,760
abducted miners,

630
00:41:14,650 --> 00:41:15,670
and seized a large amount

631
00:41:15,670 --> 00:41:17,260
of gold and gold ore.

632
00:41:18,670 --> 00:41:20,230
According to our investigation,

633
00:41:20,230 --> 00:41:21,500
all transactions of the gold mine

634
00:41:21,500 --> 00:41:22,600
were in cash.

635
00:41:22,690 --> 00:41:24,270
But since the suspect

636
00:41:24,300 --> 00:41:25,650
Li Yongqiang is dead,

637
00:41:25,790 --> 00:41:26,800
the whereabouts
of most of the illicit money

638
00:41:26,800 --> 00:41:27,980
are unknown.

639
00:41:29,150 --> 00:41:30,680
What's suspicious is...

640
00:41:31,730 --> 00:41:32,460
Li Yongqiang

641
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:33,620
was the gold mine's

642
00:41:33,780 --> 00:41:34,940
sole investor,

643
00:41:35,340 --> 00:41:36,880
but his verifiable income

644
00:41:36,990 --> 00:41:37,800
was not enough to support

645
00:41:37,800 --> 00:41:39,060
the mine's operation.

646
00:41:39,710 --> 00:41:40,690
Regarding these points,

647
00:41:40,690 --> 00:41:41,300
we are conducting

648
00:41:41,300 --> 00:41:42,760
further investigations.

649
00:41:46,500 --> 00:41:48,050
According to instructions from superiors,

650
00:41:48,050 --> 00:41:48,900
next,

651
00:41:49,280 --> 00:41:51,430
our county will join forces
with neighboring

652
00:41:51,430 --> 00:41:52,160
Boluo County

653
00:41:53,030 --> 00:41:53,890
and Zaqu County

654
00:41:54,050 --> 00:41:55,620
and carry out

655
00:41:55,650 --> 00:41:57,690
a concentrated crackdown on illegal

656
00:41:57,690 --> 00:41:59,750
gold mining activities in Bolamula.

657
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:02,200
Public Security, Armed Police,

658
00:42:02,380 --> 00:42:03,960
the local militia, and joint defense units

659
00:42:03,960 --> 00:42:05,230
will immediately form

660
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:07,060
a joint inspection task force

661
00:42:07,300 --> 00:42:08,610
to carry out

662
00:42:08,710 --> 00:42:10,300
comprehensive law enforcement operations.

663
00:42:10,300 --> 00:42:11,000
Tomorrow,

664
00:42:11,500 --> 00:42:12,610
all units must submit

665
00:42:12,610 --> 00:42:14,070
the personnel lists to me.

666
00:42:15,720 --> 00:42:16,210
Right.

667
00:42:17,570 --> 00:42:18,970
The province has already

668
00:42:19,240 --> 00:42:20,630
approved the establishment

669
00:42:20,630 --> 00:42:22,350
of the Forestry Police in our county.

670
00:42:22,350 --> 00:42:23,670
The next step is to select some people

671
00:42:23,670 --> 00:42:25,880
for training at the Provincial
Public Security Department.

672
00:42:25,880 --> 00:42:28,010
As for the specific quota allocation,

673
00:42:28,260 --> 00:42:30,720
the Public Security
and the Mountain Patrol

674
00:42:30,880 --> 00:42:32,540
can negotiate it yourselves.

675
00:42:36,800 --> 00:42:38,330
Go back and draw up the list,

676
00:42:38,380 --> 00:42:40,310
and get it to me as soon as possible.

677
00:42:47,070 --> 00:42:48,470
Your operation this time

678
00:42:48,980 --> 00:42:50,380
achieved great results,

679
00:42:53,340 --> 00:42:54,800
but the cost was also high.

680
00:43:03,870 --> 00:43:05,000
I need to make a self-criticism

681
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:06,730
regarding my previous remarks

682
00:43:07,170 --> 00:43:07,860
about the Mountain Patrol's work.
